# Coding Standards

> **Auto-attached rationale:** @docs/architecture/patterns.md
> (loads with this rule whenever you edit code under the globs above)

## Naming

- Files `kebab-case`; one primary export per file.
- Types/classes `PascalCase`; functions/vars `camelCase`; constants `UPPER_SNAKE`.
- Ports name a capability (`UserRepository`); adapters name the tech (`PostgresUserRepository`).

## Functions & flow

- Guard-clause early returns over nested conditionals.
- Pure functions in `domain`; side effects only in adapters.
- No `util`/`manager`/`helper` dumping grounds — name by behavior.

## Errors

- Throw typed domain errors, never bare strings; adapters translate transport/SDK errors into domain errors.
- Never swallow errors silently. If recovery is intended, comment why.

## Async & data

- `async/await` only — no mixed `.then()` chains.
- Validate external input at the boundary (schema). Trust nothing crossing a process edge.
- Immutability by default.

## Comments

- Match the surrounding file's density and style. Explain *why*, not *what*.
- No TODOs without an owner or a tracked task.

## Commits

- Conventional Commits 1.0.0; one task = one commit; imperative subject.
